assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Banco Patagonia S.A. provides various banking products and services in Argentina. It offers savings, retired, and minor accounts; foreign trade services, including payment orders, collection, import leasing, transfers abroad, credit letters, and financing products. The company also provides Patagonia leasing, capital marketing, and financing alternative services. In addition, it offers multi-assistance services; security boxes; credit and debit cards; and accident, personal protection, injury, health, unemployment and disability, daily income, funeral, life, consumer, women's health, pet, car, protected bag and belonging, home, motorcycle, trade, mobility, and tecno insurance products, as well as money insurance products. Further, the company provides investments for fixed-term, mutual funds, and financial trusts; and collection, payment, business cards, inter-banking, interfaces, Patagonia visa merchant, and AFIP services. It serves individuals, businesses, professionals, SMEs, agro-business clients, the public sector, and institutional clients. The company was incorporated in 1928 and is based in Buenos Aires, Argentina. Banco Patagonia S.A. is a subsidiary of Banco do Brasil S.A.
